content: Cannot use Min7b5, Aug(maj7), majb5, dim7, any altered 7th chords, or their extensions. Really limits creativity. Can sort of get away by implying alterations as bass notes, but is pretty limited since there is no way to alter the 5 or 7. Good voice leading. I like that you can export midi as played by the bot. But it's just not fun without those chords.

This is a great a app for sketching out songs quickly and easily. Once I have sketched out a song in Chordbot, I can save it as a MIDI file and import it into my workstation keyboard sequencer for further editing to complete a song. Some initial kinks: I had to install the external "File Explorer" app just so that Chordbot could load an exported .json file. Total Commander doesn't work - "file import error". Also had to uninstall Chordbot Lite for Chordbot to be listed as an 'Open with' app.
Needs a way to pick the chords from harmonized scales. Let's you select everything, but you have to either already know what you want or work out the functional harmony.

The selection of instruments, grooves, and harmonic polyphony males this the app for guitarist who want to explore lead improv over modal chord progressions.. at times some of the arpeggiated synth lines remind me of dream theater, especially when using lydian and aeolian in the progressions.. sweet app that truly deserves a lot of success.. developer kudos and keep on developing this app.. soon as things go back to normal (hopefully) I'll showcase this out in a club environment (gig) for sure
Brilliant!!

This is one of my go-to songwriting tools as a professional. I can mock up a whole arrangement with chords, drum, and bass, in a matter of minutes. No guessing if certain chords will fit together. The color coding does the trick. Bravo!!! Can't wait till you guy can expand on a few more midi patterns and maybe some new drum sound options like a Linn drum, 909, 808, etc! Amazing.
One if the best, if not the best backup band you're gonna find without having to get a 2nd mortgage or a College degree. Must have for lockdown band jam.

Fantastic app overall! Really helped me get my musical ideas out quickly. I love how detailed it is. However, I do have some suggestions to improve it further. Firstly, the audio runs way too quiet. I have to max out the volume on any device I use it on to get it to acceptable listening levels. And lastly, the way that slash chords are spelled out is incorrect. For example, an A minor triad with an E in the bass should be Am/E or Amin/E but the app shows A/E Min which can be very confusing.

You pick the key you want to use, then you pick a progression from the list, such as 6-4-1-5 or 1-4-5, etc. Then you have options to increase or decrease the number of bars in each change, copy/paste sections or add changes however you want. Then click a button that "populates" that to the song page.

Lots of chord types plus inversions and the choice to add a different root/bass note. I have lost several days of my life to this app, I suspect.

Absolutely amazing. This app is a composer's best friend. The ability to easily write chord progressions without having to write out every little part is amazing. The interface is simple yet effective without subtracting from the complexity of musicality this app brings to the table. Saving and playing songs is easy, but it's also easy to accidentally overwrite a song. Also, sometimes the visual queue for what beat you're on gets out of sync when you have lots of chord length changes in one song. Besides that, I wish there was more pad like synths to choose from, however I really do thoroughly enjoy this app. I'd recommend this to anyone who enjoys writing music at any level.

I love this app. It's just what I need to get musical ideas out quickly and easily. The interface is easy to use and there are lots of options for getting the sound you want.   That said, there are a couple of things that I think would be great additions and would make this the perfect music notepad on Android. I would really like the addition of a place to put a melody line as I'm working on chords. A single piano roll track would suffice, nothing too fancy, it's just for keeping track of things.   The other thing I'd like to see is I would like it if the chord blocks took up the space of the amount of time they represent. For instance, a chord that is eight beats takes up twice the amount of room that a four beat chord would take up. This would help phrases line up better, and improve readability.  I'm still giving this app five stars because it is still a really fantastic app even without these things, but I would be a happy musician if these things were added in.
The only thing missing is the use of roman numerals
